<section>
<title>&lt;i&gt;a&lt;/i&gt; and &lt;i&gt;an&lt;/i&gt;</title>
<sectiontitle>We use &lt;i&gt;a/an&lt;/i&gt; for jobs. We use &lt;i&gt;an&lt;/i&gt; before vowels &lt;i&gt;(a, e, i, o, u).&lt;/i&gt;</sectiontitle>
<titlesound>el_gram_1_2_1.mp3</titlesound>
<text1></text1>
<text1a>Sam's &lt;b&gt;an a&lt;/b&gt;ctor.  </text1a>
<sound1>el_gram_1_2_2.mp3</sound1>
<text2></text2>
<text2a>Pat's &lt;b&gt;an e&lt;/b&gt;ngineer.</text2a>
<sound2>el_gram_1_2_3.mp3</sound2>
<sectiontitle2>We use &lt;i&gt;a&lt;/i&gt; before consonants (&lt;i&gt;b, c, d, f, g, h&lt;/i&gt; etc.).</sectiontitle2>
<titlesound2>el_gram_1_2_4.mp3</titlesound2>
<text3></text3>
<text3a>She's&lt;b&gt; a d&lt;/b&gt;octor&lt;b&gt;.&lt;/b&gt;</text3a>
<sound3>el_gram_1_2_5.mp3</sound3>
<text4></text4>
<text4a>He's&lt;b&gt; a l&lt;/b&gt;awyer&lt;b&gt;.&lt;/b&gt;</text4a>
<sound4>el_gram_1_2_6.mp3</sound4>
</section>
